            <biogHist>
                <p>Ann Crawford née MacLucas or Douglas was born in Oban, Argyllshire around 1834,
                    the daughter of Donald MacLucas and Christine MacLucas née Campbell. Ann married
                    John Crawford (a master mariner and smack owner) in 1864 and in 1891 there are
                    four children recorded as living with them in Oban: Donald (joiner), Angus
                    (seaman), Flora (dressmaker) and John (apprentice blacksmith). The family are
                    all listed as Gaelic/English speakers.</p>
                <p>Ann Crawford died on 22 February 1917 in Argyllshire at the recorded age of 82,
                    with her grandson Angus Crawford as informant.</p>
                <p>Carmichael visited Ann in September 1890 and made sketches of two 'brooches of
                    Glenorchy' belonging to her. </p>
